<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-02-12T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-02-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="555" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d555">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">381.81/320a: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Acting American Representative to the
                                    French Committee of National Liberation at Algiers</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Chapin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-02-12T20:00:00-04:00">February 12, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>470. Reference Casablanca’s telegram no. 32, February 4, 5 p.m.
                                Please submit a full report at once, on reported action of Combined
                                Food Committee at Algiers in insisting that French authorities
                                requisition entire olive crop of persons under American protection
                                in French Morocco. The Department would take a serious view of any
                                attempt to infringe the treaty rights of American <hi rend="italic">ressortissants</hi> in Morocco. The Department has emphasized
                                repeatedly that no decrees promulgated in Morocco are applicable to
                                American protégés until this Government’s consent is conveyed to the
                                Resident General.</p>
                            <p>Repeat to Casablanca.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>